Headquarters Regions: East Coast, New England, Northeastern US
Full Description: Launched in 2009, Archview Investment Group LP is an institutional alternative investment firm focused on event-driven credit opportunities within the capital structures of stressed, distressed and out of favor companies. Founding Principals, Jeff Jacob and John Humphrey, have invested, managed risk and built businesses together since 1995. The core of our investment team has managed event-driven credit investments together since 2004. We view our team-based, collaborative culture as a differentiator that has contributed to our firm’s stability and success. We seek to generate alpha by combining deep industry and restructuring knowledge with rigorous fundamental credit analysis to uncover absolute and relative mispricings within capital structures. Our goal is to invest in the part of a capital structure that can provide the best risk/return opportunities while employing our time-tested discipline for capital preservation. We do not employ leverage as we believe it does not make an investment better, just riskier. We pride ourselves on our ability to partner with companies and create solutions, allowing our investors to gain exposure to company-specific opportunities that are not generally correlated to the overall direction of the markets.

If you or someone you love find yourself facing a charge, you need an advocate on your side who will treat you like a person and who understands how to protect your rights and help you fight back. Even after you supposedly pay back your debt to society, a criminal conviction will stick with you in the form of a criminal record that can make it more difficult for you to get a job, find a place to live, secure a loan, and more. The best way to protect your future? Fight back. Since 2005, founder Jeffrey L.
